column3: str

Yubli is waiting on a shipment to arrive.

※Please note that the difficulty of this quest has been synced to your current level. Furthermore, you may not proceed with a class or job that is different from when you accepted this quest.
Speak with the Moblin porter.
Pick up the crate of goldwork.
Carry the crate of goldwork to the supply officer.
Speak with Yubli.
An important shipment has just arrived from Earthenshire, delivered to the nearest wharf by punutiy. The problem, however, is that the crate is <Emphasis>extremely</Emphasis> heavy.
I'd like to have it moved before arriving customers trip over it, but our Moblin porter appears to be struggling with the weight.
Could you go down to the wharf and lend a hand? The porter will tell you where the crate needs to be.
Special Advisor! Thank you for coming to handhelp floppyarm Mobbie!

Potsworn goldwork is a popular choice for Kozama'uka memorykeeping! But a crate holding many goldcrafts is too much bulkyweight for one Moblin to move. Please, he needs an ironarm adventurer to carry it to the supply officer!
Deliver the crate of goldwork to the supply officer waiting outside the travel agency storehouse before the time runs out.
You will have sixty seconds to complete the task. Should you fail, return to the starting location and begin anew.
That crate is too heavy for Mobbie, but the supply officer will be waiting! Please make the delivery with careful eyewatchings and quicksteps!
What's wrong? Was the crate too much bulkyweight even for you? Maybe you just need a shortrest before trying again!
Something else tickling your braincage? Mobbie is happy to leave the potsworn goldcraft in your capable helphands!
The goods we ordered should have been delivered by now...
Collect the Moblin porter's crate of goldwork from the wharf and deliver it to the supply officer.
Ah, is that the shipment from Earthenshire? Thank you for bringing it in. I would have picked it up myself, but sorting out our inventory has kept me chained to the storehouse.

Potsworn craft is in high demand, and maintaining a steady supply has been a logistical headache, to say the least. We've just had a customer asking about availability, so I'd like to get this goldwork on the shelves sooner rather than later.
Thank you for taking care of that delivery so quickly!

The potsworn's goldwork we sell in our shop is highly sought after by customers with more...expensive taste. It seems a memento like this becomes all the more special for having found it in such memorable surrounds.
Which is all to say that if we're not careful, our stock soon runs dangerously low. I'd be grateful if you could help out again should we need a hand!
